<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/43526399-assaph-mehr">Assaph Mehr</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">The women in the book like to think so :-)<br/><br/>There are a few women in the novels. Some are demure, some are opinionated. All written as individual human <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">The women in the book like to think so :-)<br /><br />There are a few women in the novels. Some are demure, some are opinionated. All written as individual human beings, with their own agendas and lives, making their way in a society based on ancient Rome.<br /><br />You can even read an <a href="https://egretia.com/2018/08/29/meet-aemilia/" rel="nofollow noopener">interview with one of them</a>.<br /><br />Make of it what you will. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
