<div id="review_1825511278" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1825511278" />
    <a title="Heidi" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7538529-heidi"><img alt="Heidi" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1335627261p2/7538529.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1825511278?book_show_action=true">Nov 29, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Heidi" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Heidi" href="/user/show/7538529-heidi">Heidi</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/29500704-murder-in-absentia">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1825511278" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer850563557954922132">I was pleasantly surprised by this book after a discussion about fish sauce and whether or not it was Felix&apos;s favorite food with the author. Assaph gifted me with this e-book so that I could find out the answer. I enjoyed following Felix along during his investigation of the murder of a young Egretian man. The book captivated my interest and I found I was having a harder and harder time putting the book down. I loved the historical setting and the place that Assaph created. There are some very i</span>
  <span id="freeText850563557954922132" style="display:none">I was pleasantly surprised by this book after a discussion about fish sauce and whether or not it was Felix's favorite food with the author. Assaph gifted me with this e-book so that I could find out the answer. I enjoyed following Felix along during his investigation of the murder of a young Egretian man. The book captivated my interest and I found I was having a harder and harder time putting the book down. I loved the historical setting and the place that Assaph created. There are some very interesting characters. The storyline is full of unexpected turns, providing a true mystery. However, Mr. Mehr, I still cannot conclusively say that fish sauce is Felix's favorite food. You are going to have to keep writing about him so that at some point I can come to a unarguable decision on this matter! Also, I must know more about Felix's past and what happened with the woman he loved.</span>
  <a data-text-id="850563557954922132" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


